ure-wrap"><figure id="fig15c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig15c.jpeg" height="1800" width="1179" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig15c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig15d.jpeg" height="1602" width="1452" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig15d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig16.jpeg" height="1359" width="1566" aria-labelledby="fig16" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16</span> Diaphragmatic tear in a 10-year-old child who was involved in a motor vehicle accident. Frontal chest radiograph shows elevation of the left hemidiaphragm. There is intrathoracic herniation of the stomach, as indicated by the location of the nasogastric tube (straight arrow). The medial well-defined line (curved arrow) probably represents the stomach wall. At surgery, the diaphragm was found to be torn centrally. The opacification of the left hemithorax represents a combination of hemothorax and compressive atelectasis of the left lung above the superomedial stomach wall. There is associated mediastinal shift.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig16">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig17a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1782" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig17a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig17b.jpeg" height="1678" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig17b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig18a.jpeg" height="1312" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig18a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig18b.jpeg" height="1297" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig18b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig19a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1547" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig19a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig19b.jpeg" height="1656" width="1378" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig19b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig19c.jpeg" height="1492" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.307105046&amp;id=fig19c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.307105046/asset/images/105046fig20.jpeg" height="1296" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig20" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20</span> Secondary involvement of the diaphragm by an adjacent malignant tumor in a 9-year-old child. Axial CT image shows a minimally but heterogeneously enhancing mass in the right adrenal gland (straight arrow). There is thickening of the right diaphragmatic crus (arrowheads), a finding suggestive of secondary involvement. Pathologic analysis demonstrated an adrenal rhabdoid tumor. Cu